A React Application
Requirements
Node.js and npm
How to Run
Install Node.js and npm

Download and install from nodejs.org.
Create a React Project

Open terminal and run
bash
Copy code
npx create-react-app chat-app
Navigate into the chat-app
bash
Copy code
cd chat-app
Install Dependencies

Run
bash
Copy code
npm install @chatscope/chat-ui-kit-react @chatscope/chat-ui-kit-styles
Add API Key

Create a file in the root of your project
Copy code
npm start
The app should open in your default web browser.
Streamlit App
Prerequisites
Python and pip
How to run
Install Python:

Download and install from python.org.
Set Up A Virtual Environment:

Create a virtual environment:
bash
Copy code
python -m venv myenv
Active the virtual environment:
On Windows:
bash
Copy code
myenv\Scripts\activate
On macOS/Linux:
bash
Copy code
source myenv/bin/activate
Install Dependencies:
streamlit run app.py
The application will open in a new browser tab
This is an easy to read, step-by-step guide for setup and usage of, first the React and then the Streamlit application.


